{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-18",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_18_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 18 - The Fall-Guy",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 7,
  "page_total": 9,
  "page_start_sec": 1471.712,
  "page_end_sec": 1713.96,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.691,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 1471.712,
      "end": 1473.18,
      "text": "Gutman looked as if he did not believe",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1473.18,
      "end": 1474.84,
      "text": "he could have heard what he had heard."
    },
    {
      "start": 1475.46,
      "end": 1475.88,
      "text": "He asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1475.96,
      "end": 1477.58,
      "text": "\"'Do what?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1478.496,
      "end": 1479.84,
      "text": "\"'Give the police Cairo.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1480.992,
      "end": 1482.4,
      "text": "Gutman seemed about to laugh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1482.58,
      "end": 1483.64,
      "text": "but he did not laugh."
    },
    {
      "start": 1484.544,
      "end": 1485.56,
      "text": "Finally he exclaimed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1485.99,
      "end": 1486.94,
      "text": "\"'Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1487.18,
      "end": 1487.92,
      "text": "by God,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1488.1,
      "end": 1488.5,
      "text": "sir,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1489.24,
      "end": 1490.4,
      "text": "in an uncertain voice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1491.84,
      "end": 1494.64,
      "text": "\"'It's not as good as giving them the punk,' Spade said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1495.424,
      "end": 1496.42,
      "text": "\"'Cairo's not a gunman,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1496.52,
      "end": 1497.7,
      "text": "and he carries a .38,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1497.92,
      "end": 1500.72,
      "text": "while Jacoby and Thursby were cut down by larger"
    },
    {
      "start": 1500.82,
      "end": 1501.14,
      "text": "bullets."
    },
    {
      "start": 1502.02,
      "end": 1504.38,
      "text": "That means we'd have to go to some trouble framing him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1504.46,
      "end": 1505.48,
      "text": "but that's better than"
    },
    {
      "start": 1505.56,
      "end": 1507.03,
      "text": "giving the police nobody.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1508.992,
      "end": 1511.58,
      "text": "Cairo cried in a voice shrill with indignation.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1512.63,
      "end": 1513.8,
      "text": "\"'Suppose we give them you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1513.94,
      "end": 1514.12,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1514.18,
      "end": 1514.46,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1514.64,
      "end": 1515.92,
      "text": "or Miss O'Shaughnessy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1516.08,
      "end": 1518.08,
      "text": "How about that if you're so set"
    },
    {
      "start": 1518.08,
      "end": 1519.35,
      "text": "on giving them somebody?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1520.704,
      "end": 1523.4,
      "text": "Spade smiled at the Levantine and answered him calmly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1524.88,
      "end": 1525.98,
      "text": "\"'You people want the Falcon.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1526.22,
      "end": 1527.24,
      "text": "I've got it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1528.128,
      "end": 1530.5,
      "text": "I'm asking for a fall guy as part of my price.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1531.54,
      "end": 1532.59,
      "text": "As for Miss O'Shaughnessy—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1534.34,
      "end": 1536.48,
      "text": "His dispassionate glance moved to her white,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1536.65,
      "end": 1537.46,
      "text": "perplexed face for"
    },
    {
      "start": 1537.6,
      "end": 1539.14,
      "text": "moments and then back to Cairo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1539.32,
      "end": 1541.54,
      "text": "and his shoulders rose and fell a"
    },
    {
      "start": 1541.64,
      "end": 1542.48,
      "text": "fraction of an inch."
    },
    {
      "start": 1544.04,
      "end": 1545.62,
      "text": "\"'If you think she can be rigged for the part,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1545.82,
      "end": 1546.98,
      "text": "I'm perfectly willing"
    },
    {
      "start": 1546.98,
      "end": 1548.288,
      "text": "to talk it over with you.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1549.34,
      "end": 1550.84,
      "text": "The girl put her hands to her throat,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1551.08,
      "end": 1552.08,
      "text": "uttered a short,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1552.12,
      "end": 1552.78,
      "text": "strangled cry,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1553.02,
      "end": 1554.22,
      "text": "and edged away from him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1554.78,
      "end": 1555.38,
      "text": "Cairo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1555.58,
      "end": 1557.3,
      "text": "his face and body twitching with"
    },
    {
      "start": 1557.4,
      "end": 1557.8,
      "text": "excitement,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1557.86,
      "end": 1558.36,
      "text": "exclaimed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1559.32,
      "end": 1562.42,
      "text": "\"'You seem to forget that you are not in a position to insist on any",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1562.5,
      "end": 1563.072,
      "text": "price.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1564.064,
      "end": 1564.72,
      "text": "Spade laughed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1564.96,
      "end": 1565.48,
      "text": "a short,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1565.58,
      "end": 1566.54,
      "text": "derisive snort."
    },
    {
      "start": 1567.776,
      "end": 1568.26,
      "text": "Gutman said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1568.5,
      "end": 1570.91,
      "text": "in a voice that tried to make firmness ingratiating,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1571.936,
      "end": 1572.38,
      "text": "\"'Come now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1572.42,
      "end": 1572.76,
      "text": "gentlemen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1573.0,
      "end": 1575.36,
      "text": "let's keep our discussion on a friendly basis."
    },
    {
      "start": 1576.38,
      "end": 1579.58,
      "text": "But there certainly is,' he was addressing Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1580.16,
      "end": 1581.18,
      "text": "\"'something in what Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1581.26,
      "end": 1581.84,
      "text": "Cairo says."
    },
    {
      "start": 1583.14,
      "end": 1585.64,
      "text": "You must take into consideration the—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1585.9,
      "end": 1587.136,
      "text": "\"'Like hell I must!'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1588.192,
      "end": 1590.92,
      "text": "Spade flung his words out with a brutal sort of carelessness",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1591.08,
      "end": 1593.02,
      "text": "that gave them more weight than they could have got"
    },
    {
      "start": 1593.1,
      "end": 1595.06,
      "text": "from dramatic emphasis or from loudness."
    },
    {
      "start": 1595.98,
      "end": 1596.98,
      "text": "\"'If you kill me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1597.48,
      "end": 1598.43,
      "text": "how are you going to get the bird?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1599.28,
      "end": 1600.86,
      "text": "If I know you can't afford to kill me till",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1600.86,
      "end": 1601.34,
      "text": "you have it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1601.52,
      "end": 1603.936,
      "text": "how are you going to scare me into giving it to you?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1605.184,
      "end": 1607.78,
      "text": "Goodman cocked his head to the left and considered these questions.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1608.34,
      "end": 1610.76,
      "text": "His eyes twinkled between puckered lids."
    },
    {
      "start": 1611.02,
      "end": 1613.52,
      "text": "Presently he gave his genial answer."
    },
    {
      "start": 1614.54,
      "end": 1615.06,
      "text": "\"'Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1615.08,
      "end": 1615.32,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1615.5,
      "end": 1617.58,
      "text": "there are other means of persuasion"
    },
    {
      "start": 1617.58,
      "end": 1619.6,
      "text": "besides killing or threatening to kill.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1619.79,
      "end": 1622.06,
      "text": "\"'Sure,' Spade agreed."
    },
    {
      "start": 1623.104,
      "end": 1624.72,
      "text": "\"'But they're not much good unless the threat",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1624.72,
      "end": 1626.86,
      "text": "of death is behind them to hold the victim down."
    },
    {
      "start": 1627.62,
      "end": 1628.26,
      "text": "See what I mean?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1629.02,
      "end": 1630.42,
      "text": "If you try anything I don't like,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1630.52,
      "end": 1631.64,
      "text": "I won't stand for it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1632.26,
      "end": 1634.76,
      "text": "I'll make it a matter of your having to call it off or kill me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1635.2,
      "end": 1636.928,
      "text": "knowing you can't afford to kill me.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1638.048,
      "end": 1639.28,
      "text": "\"'I see what you mean,'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1639.904,
      "end": 1640.52,
      "text": "Cutman chuckled."
    },
    {
      "start": 1641.984,
      "end": 1642.92,
      "text": "\"'That is an attitude,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1643.1,
      "end": 1643.36,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1643.54,
      "end": 1646.54,
      "text": "that calls for the most delicate judgment on both sides,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1646.94,
      "end": 1647.48,
      "text": "because,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1647.84,
      "end": 1648.4,
      "text": "as you know,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1648.48,
      "end": 1648.66,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1648.84,
      "end": 1652.32,
      "text": "men are likely to forget in the heat of action just what they"
    },
    {
      "start": 1652.32,
      "end": 1653.34,
      "text": "can and can't afford,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1653.62,
      "end": 1656.192,
      "text": "and let their emotions carry them away.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1657.408,
      "end": 1659.28,
      "text": "Spade was all smiling blandness.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1660.8,
      "end": 1662.92,
      "text": "\"'That's the trick from my side,' he said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1663.48,
      "end": 1665.84,
      "text": "\"'to make my play strong enough that it ties you up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1665.92,
      "end": 1667.84,
      "text": "but not strong enough to make you mad"
    },
    {
      "start": 1667.96,
      "end": 1669.95,
      "text": "enough to bump me off against your better judgment.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1671.552,
      "end": 1672.72,
      "text": "Gutman said fondly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1673.472,
      "end": 1673.9,
      "text": "\"'By gad,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1673.96,
      "end": 1674.22,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1674.44,
      "end": 1675.72,
      "text": "you're a character.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1677.4,
      "end": 1679.64,
      "text": "Joel Cairo jumped up from his chair and went",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1679.64,
      "end": 1681.62,
      "text": "around behind the boy and behind Gutman's"
    },
    {
      "start": 1681.7,
      "end": 1681.82,
      "text": "chair."
    },
    {
      "start": 1682.96,
      "end": 1685.06,
      "text": "He bent over the back of Gutman's chair and,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1685.1,
      "end": 1686.86,
      "text": "screaming his mouth and the fat man's"
    },
    {
      "start": 1686.86,
      "end": 1688.0,
      "text": "ear with his empty hand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1688.12,
      "end": 1688.68,
      "text": "whispered."
    },
    {
      "start": 1689.92,
      "end": 1691.02,
      "text": "Gutman listened attentively,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1691.22,
      "end": 1692.16,
      "text": "shutting his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 1693.344,
      "end": 1695.06,
      "text": "Spade grinned at Brigitte O'Shaughnessy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1695.24,
      "end": 1697.52,
      "text": "Her lips smiled feebly in response."
    },
    {
      "start": 1698.02,
      "end": 1698.84,
      "text": "There was"
    },
    {
      "start": 1698.84,
      "end": 1700.06,
      "text": "no change in her eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 1700.54,
      "end": 1701.82,
      "text": "They did not lose their numb,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1701.98,
      "end": 1702.7,
      "text": "fearful stare."
    },
    {
      "start": 1704.54,
      "end": 1705.18,
      "text": "Spade turned to the boy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1706.48,
      "end": 1707.64,
      "text": "\"'Two to one they're selling you out,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1707.74,
      "end": 1708.1,
      "text": "son.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1709.02,
      "end": 1710.24,
      "text": "The boy did not say anything.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1710.56,
      "end": 1712.88,
      "text": "A trembling in his knees began to shake"
    },
    {
      "start": 1712.88,
      "end": 1713.96,
      "text": "the knees of his trousers."
    }
  ]
}